metadata.name: Kink #172
metadata.description:
Kink is a representation of the idea that creative evolution is born from the subtle twists, turns, and kinks. 

A base element is manipulated, bent and reshaped, subjecting it to the artistic equivalent of a kink. When several such ideas converge, they give birth to a fresh concept altogether through an evolution in thought and form.

Implemented in JS, this code utilizes the Perlin.js and Simple-noise.js libraries.

Press p to save a PNG of the image in full screen. Press s to save a single complete SVG file for plotting.

And this is a redeemable project in case you‚Äôd like to receive a physical plot!

metadata.name: Monsoon #397
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: Brosser #142
metadata.description:
Exploring generative brush strokes to simulate real life paintings. 

- A selection of 19 different palettes
- 4 different drawing styles
- Randomized "color swap" between the primary and secondary colors in each palette

Several other factors determine the output of a piece, including angles, depth, brush length, and brush weight, among others.
